Subject: [redhat] makefile: switch secureboot kernel image signing to release keys

Message-id: <1474573484-15115-3-git-send-email-aquini@redhat.com>
Patchwork-id: 158327
O-Subject: [RHEL7 PATCH 2/2] redhat: makefile: switch secureboot kernel image signing to release keys
Bugzilla:
RH-Acked-by: Ivan Vecera <ivecera@redhat.com>
RH-Acked-by: Jeremy McNicoll <jmcnicol@redhat.com>
RH-Acked-by: Prarit Bhargava <prarit@redhat.com>
RH-Acked-by: Herton R. Krzesinski <herton@redhat.com>
RH-Acked-by: Jarod Wilson <jarod@redhat.com>

Since the next build should be RC we need to flip RELEASED_KERNEL to 1,
so that the build uses the production UEFI secureboot keys to sign kernel
image instead of the beta/devel one currently in use.

This is a RHEL7-only patch, not upstream.

Brew: https://brewweb.engineering.redhat.com/brew/taskinfo?taskID=11799431
Test: https://beaker.engineering.redhat.com/jobs/1518937

Signed-off-by: Rafael Aquini <aquini@redhat.com>

diff --git a/redhat/Makefile.common b/redhat/Makefile.common
index 1cd68b1..7808127 100644
--- a/redhat/Makefile.common
+++ b/redhat/Makefile.common
@@ -24,7 +24,7 @@ FILTERDIFF:=/usr/bin/filterdiff -x '*redhat/*' -x '*/.gitignore' -x '*/makefile'
 # 0 : pre-release (devel) secureboot keys are used for signing
 # 1 : release (RC/GA) secureboot keys are used for signing
 #
-RELEASED_KERNEL:=0
+RELEASED_KERNEL:=1
 
 STAMP_VERSION:=$(KVERSION)
 
